00:37:49.390 --> 00:37:50.970
I do have one question though.

00:37:50.970 --> 00:37:54.470
So you spoke a little bit
about getting thoughts spiraled

00:37:54.470 --> 00:37:56.860
in your head about
negativity-- building up

00:37:56.860 --> 00:37:59.680
to scenarios that
actually never happen.

00:37:59.680 --> 00:38:01.930
I know my family is
specifically guilty of doing

00:38:01.930 --> 00:38:02.854
this kind of thing.

00:38:02.854 --> 00:38:05.520
So I'm really interested in like
to hear from you, specific tips

00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:07.520
or tricks to help people
to stop themselves

00:38:07.520 --> 00:38:10.540
from getting into a place where
they start thinking like that.

00:38:10.540 --> 00:38:11.540
ARIANNA HUFFINGTON: Yes.

00:38:11.540 --> 00:38:16.115
So first of all, if
we kind of recognize

00:38:16.115 --> 00:38:19.600
that that voice
is not who we are.

00:38:19.600 --> 00:38:23.020
And that's why I call it
the obnoxious roommate

00:38:23.020 --> 00:38:25.340
living in my head.

00:38:25.340 --> 00:38:30.470
And every time that
comes up, that voice, I

00:38:30.470 --> 00:38:32.165
think a sense of
humor really helps.

00:38:34.740 --> 00:38:40.220
And making it clear that
thoughts are not facts.

00:38:40.220 --> 00:38:43.060
And thoughts are not you.

00:38:43.060 --> 00:38:48.810
So there's that thing going
on, and if you approach it

00:38:48.810 --> 00:38:54.540
like a sort of a toddler,
kind of screaming and being

00:38:54.540 --> 00:38:57.510
disruptive, but it's not who
you are, and it's not fact.

00:38:57.510 --> 00:39:00.580
It begins to weaken the
power it has on you.

00:39:00.580 --> 00:39:04.150
I promise you, I had the most
obnoxious roommate living

00:39:04.150 --> 00:39:05.550
in my head.

00:39:05.550 --> 00:39:06.980
Very self- judgmental.

00:39:06.980 --> 00:39:11.790
And now she only makes
guest appearances.

00:39:11.790 --> 00:39:18.500
And so the energy that
became available to me

00:39:18.500 --> 00:39:21.710
when that voice
subsided is amazing.

00:39:21.710 --> 00:39:25.670
Because we look at the our
life in terms of time chunks,

00:39:25.670 --> 00:39:28.880
but really it's
all about energy.

00:39:28.880 --> 00:39:31.800
When you are operating
at 100% of your energy,

00:39:31.800 --> 00:39:36.220
you can get stuff
done in one hour that

00:39:36.220 --> 00:39:39.730
otherwise would take you a day.

00:39:39.730 --> 00:39:44.310
And a function of
good energy isn't

00:39:44.310 --> 00:39:48.320
just how much sleep we
get, or how rested we are.

00:39:48.320 --> 00:39:51.060
It's also what we're
doing with our thoughts.

00:39:51.060 --> 00:39:53.010
And what we're doing
with our minds.

00:39:53.010 --> 00:40:00.200
But I promise you that you can
evict the obnoxious roommate

00:40:00.200 --> 00:40:00.965
almost entirely.

